<item>
            <title>[SPR-13579] Add conversion support for java.time.Duration</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-13579</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Java 8&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;java.time.Duration&lt;/tt&gt; is a good choice for defining durations of time, and arguably better than using a &lt;tt&gt;long&lt;/tt&gt; with a property name to specify the units.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be good to support conversion from a &lt;tt&gt;String&lt;/tt&gt; to make it easier to use beans that use this in their API.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="66333">SPR-13579</key>
            <summary>Add conversion support for java.time.Duration</summary>
